# GCP VM Command Constraints

The GCP Compute Engine VM (Ubuntu) does not grant sudo access to the user `kemet_dugue`. When generating shell commands for the VM:

- Never use `sudo` in any command
- Install npm packages locally (project-level) instead of globally (`npm install pm2`, not `npm install -g pm2`)
- Use `npx` to run locally installed CLI tools
- Do not attempt to bind to privileged ports (below 1024); use port 3001 instead
- Do not use `iptables`, `systemctl`, or other commands requiring root
